Description

This repository contains beginner-friendly Python programs focused on building core programming logic using conditional statements and loops. It is designed for students who are starting with Python and want to strengthen problem-solving skills.

Concepts Covered
Conditional Statements (if, elif, else)
Loops (while)
Basic Input/Output
Logical Thinking & Problem Solving
Programs Included
Even or Odd Checker using conditional statements
Positive, Negative, or Zero identification
Print numbers from 1 to N using while loop
Sum of first N natural numbers
Password retry system with limited attempts
Multiplication table generation
Key Learnings
How to take user input and process it
Writing decision-making logic using conditions
Using loops to repeat tasks efficiently
Building simple real-world logic (like password validation)
Improving coding clarity with meaningful variable names
